            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-31T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="318" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d318">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On November 17 the High Commissioners met with <persName corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName> again and discussed <hi rend="italic">inter alia</hi>
                    modifications of the reparations program. <persName corresp="#p_RNA1">Robertson</persName>, as Chairman, informed the West German Chancellor
                    concerning the plants that would be removed from the reparations list in the
                    synthetic oil, rubber and steel industries, and in Berlin. A record of this
                    meeting was transmitted in telegram 4083, November 18, from Frankfurt, not
                    printed (860.00/11–1849).</p>
            </div>
        </body>
